  "texts": [
    "Relative LLM judge: The relative judge compares two or more LLM responses, and ranks them or selects the best one.",
    "It is commonly used in ranking-based assessments, preference modeling, and pairwise comparisons.",
    "Formally, let (x, y 1, y 2) be a prompt-responses tuple from two judged LLMs.",
    "The relative judge maps (x, y 1, y 2) to (e, b)",
    ", where e is the rationale that judges y 1 and y 2 given x, and b ∈ {0, 1} is the associated relative preference score."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}